Model¶

In [17]:
name2id = {v:k for k,v in enumerate(codes)}
void_code = name2id['Void']

# custom metric: sometimes they label the pixels as void so we want to remove those. 
# this metric is called the camvid feature
def acc_camvid(input, target):
    target = target.squeeze(1)
    mask = target != void_code
    return (input.argmax(dim=1)[mask]==target[mask]).float().mean()
In [18]:
metrics=acc_camvid

# accuracy here is the sum of pixels correctly classified over all pixels
# metrics=accuracy
In [19]:
wd=1e-2
In [20]:
# unet architecture used here
learn = unet_learner(data, models.resnet34, metrics=metrics, wd=wd)

# cyclical learning rate - increase learning rate at the start, and then reduce it as you get closer to the solution
# helps the model to explore the whole function surface for areas where the loss is low, but a 'flatter' bit where 
# the model will generalise better

# this means that the learning rate finder is passing in the maximum learning rate
